Sentencas: Cobalt manganese spinels have recently been studied as potential candidates for protective-conducting coatings on ferritic stainless steel interconnects for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (IT-SOFCs) applications.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: Mn1+xCo2-xO4 (x=0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0 and 1.5) spinels were synthesized using EDTA-gel processes to optimize the performance of high-quality spinel protective-conducting films developed on steel interconnects.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: The structure, morphology and the electrical conductivity of the obtained bulk samples were investigated using XRD, SEM and EIS, respectively.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: The obtained MnCo2O4 and Mn-1.25Co1.75O4 oxides were cubic spinels over the whole temperature range (373 <= T <= 1073K).
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: The other samples exhibited both tetragonal and cubic structures with higher cubic phase content at increasing temperatures.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: The prepared Mn1+xCo2-xO4 (0 <= x <= 0.5) spinels exhibited desirable electrical conductivity; the highest conductivity at 1073 K was found for MnCo2O4(132.2 S cm(-1)), whereas the lowest one (1.9 S cm(-1)) for Mn2.5Co0.5O4.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes

Sentencas: Tetragonal cubic phase transition depended on spinel composition, and its influence on the electrical properties of the spinel solid solutions was studied over a wide temperature range.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical properties of Mn1+xCO2-xO4(0≤x≤1.5) spinels synthesized using EDTA-gel processes
